place.name: STERT
place.gazetteerText: STERT, a chapelry in Urchfont parish, Wilts; on the Mid Wilts railway, 2½ miles ESE of Devizes. Post town, Devizes. Acres, 638. Real property, £1,338. Pop., 184. Houses, 40. The living is annexed to Urchfont. The church was built in 1846. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
